WEBVTT

00:02.043 --> 00:03.586
<i>My brother and I always dreamt</i>

00:03.586 --> 00:05.338
<i>of becoming the greatest of all time.</i>

00:05.463 --> 00:08.049
<i>And for one of us,
that dream was about to come true.</i>

00:14.305 --> 00:19.644
<i>And so the 2031 championship
comes down to one last possession.</i>

00:19.936 --> 00:23.606
<i>Bell bringing it up, crosses him over,
shakes free at mid-court.</i>

00:23.773 --> 00:26.735
<i>- He elevates. Finishes. And a foul!</i>

00:26.985 --> 00:30.405
<i>But, oh, he's down.
Looks like he hurt his shooting hand.</i>

00:31.448 --> 00:33.908
<i>Wait a minute. He is staying in the game.</i>

00:34.659 --> 00:35.910
<i>Point three seconds left.</i>

00:36.077 --> 00:40.040
<i>It's all up to this rookie MVP
to make the shot.</i>

00:40.582 --> 00:42.625
Game on the line, kid. Don't brick it.

00:42.959 --> 00:47.297
<i>Every GOAT needs
to have talent, timing, and teachers.</i>

00:48.214 --> 00:50.508
<i>Dad's basketball rule number 21.</i>

00:51.176 --> 00:52.260
<i>Plan to win.</i>

00:52.677 --> 00:53.720
<i>Play your game.</i>

00:57.557 --> 01:00.351
<i>Prepare to adjust.</i>

01:01.686 --> 01:04.189
That's a bad look, Filthy. Go, baby.

01:04.355 --> 01:05.356
Let's do it.

01:11.571 --> 01:13.573
Ooh!

01:13.698 --> 01:16.367
Must be a dentist
'cause that was in his grill!

01:16.367 --> 01:17.744
<i>Ball was our life.</i>

01:17.869 --> 01:20.747
<i>There was only one word
in our dictionary, win.</i>

01:20.914 --> 01:23.208
I'm dribblin' at the top of the key.

01:23.833 --> 01:26.795
I'm movin' and groovin'.
I'm poppin' and rockin'.

01:27.003 --> 01:29.214
Why you bumpin'? Why you lockin'?

01:29.339 --> 01:31.132
Man, take this thumpin'.

01:31.382 --> 01:34.094
- Bro, just play ball, man! What you got?
- This right here for you.

01:34.219 --> 01:36.846
<i>Muhammad Ali
and Deion Sanders didn't just talk.</i>

01:37.013 --> 01:40.767
<i>They were truth tellers and day dreamers.
Top of their game rhyme schemers.</i>

01:40.767 --> 01:43.061
<i>Just like me. Words matter, bro.</i>

01:45.230 --> 01:49.359
<i>Josh Bell's the name.
Filthy McNasty's the claim to fame.</i>

01:49.359 --> 01:51.611
<i>Dad dubbed me that
'cause my game's acclaimed.</i>

01:51.736 --> 01:54.656
<i>So downright dirty,
it'll put you to shame.</i>

01:55.573 --> 01:56.699
Come on, baby. Let's go.

01:57.242 --> 01:59.994
<i>Jordan Bell,
also known as JB.</i>

01:59.994 --> 02:04.624
<i>When he shoots from deep, believe.
His jumper falls like leaves.</i>

02:12.465 --> 02:15.760
Battle of the Bells. Game point!
Let's go, Filthy!

02:15.760 --> 02:19.389
<i>Chuck Bell's Da Man.
Balled from LA to Japan.</i>

02:19.389 --> 02:23.393
<i>Game was super bad.
But now he's just our super dad.</i>

02:24.310 --> 02:25.895
Come on, man.
You got to do better than that.

02:28.356 --> 02:31.276
<i>The Crossover.
Staple of all great ballers.</i>

02:31.484 --> 02:33.945
<i>Iverson, Kyrie, D-Will.</i>

02:34.070 --> 02:37.240
<i>A simple move where a player
quickly dribbles from one hand to another.</i>

02:37.240 --> 02:40.451
<i>As in, think I'm going one way, but...</i>

02:44.706 --> 02:47.375
Booyah!
Yeah, come on, now.

02:47.375 --> 02:49.002
- Come on! Ah!
-  Get some crutches,

02:49.127 --> 02:50.628
- he broke both of his ankles!
- Yeah!

02:50.628 --> 02:54.591
Uh-uh, uh-uh. No. Uh-uh-uh.
Basketball rule number one.

02:54.841 --> 02:58.803
In the game of life, family is the court,
basketball is the heart.

02:58.803 --> 03:01.055
Always leave your heart on the court.

03:01.222 --> 03:02.724
Win or lose, y'all play together.

03:06.227 --> 03:08.813
- All right, boys. Now, if I make this?

03:09.397 --> 03:10.815
- Donuts.
- All right, let's see.

03:19.073 --> 03:21.326
<i>What a difference</i>

03:22.202 --> 03:24.412
<i>A day makes</i>

03:25.205 --> 03:28.833
<i>Twenty-four little hours</i>

03:30.126 --> 03:33.421
<i>Brought the sun and the flowers</i>

03:34.923 --> 03:38.676
<i>Where there used to be rain</i>

03:38.843 --> 03:43.097
<i>My yesterday was blue, dear</i>

03:43.097 --> 03:44.557
Hey, you know
who's better than Kobe?

03:44.557 --> 03:46.226
Who?
Michael Jordan.

03:46.226 --> 03:47.518
What?
There you go.

03:47.644 --> 03:49.312
Better than the Mamba?
Yeah.

03:51.814 --> 03:54.651
...ever! They visualized victory!
MJ made it happen.

03:54.776 --> 03:56.402
<i>Dr. Crystal Bell.</i>

03:56.694 --> 04:01.449
<i>All-star scholar. Fam shot-caller.
Beloved, dear Mama.</i>

04:02.116 --> 04:05.954
Mom! Please tell these guys,
in your opinion, who is the GOAT?

04:06.079 --> 04:09.165
Oh. That's easy. Chuck "Da Man" Bell.

04:09.290 --> 04:10.625
- Am I right?
That's right.

04:11.376 --> 04:12.585
Baby, you know the rule.

04:12.961 --> 04:14.587
No basketball at the table.

04:15.004 --> 04:17.840
And you two, homework, dinner, then bed.

04:18.258 --> 04:20.885
Wait, what about dessert? Dad won donuts.

04:21.219 --> 04:22.220
Okay.

04:23.680 --> 04:25.932
- You gotta play my game.
- Let's go!

04:26.057 --> 04:27.976
Spelling bee. "Aerial."

04:30.144 --> 04:31.813
- All right.
- Oh, no, no. I was thinking.

04:31.813 --> 04:33.982
- I was thinkin' of the word. "Ariel."
Uh-huh. Uh-huh.

04:34.190 --> 04:38.361
A-R-I-E-L. Was a little mermaid
who lived under the sea.

04:38.778 --> 04:42.031
<i>Under the sea, under the sea</i>

04:42.031 --> 04:45.368
You gonna be living under the sea
if I don't hear it spelled correctly.

04:45.576 --> 04:46.786
"Aerial."

04:47.287 --> 04:49.205
A-E-R-I-A-L.

04:49.497 --> 04:53.376
<i>As in, flying up above
As in, birds in the air</i>

04:53.584 --> 04:57.255
<i>As in, Filthy soars to places
Eagles wouldn't dare</i>

04:58.214 --> 05:00.300
Okay.

05:00.425 --> 05:02.302
Seems like someone's been studying.

05:02.760 --> 05:04.595
- Thank you.
- And someone hasn't.

05:05.930 --> 05:08.308
Your English teacher tells me
that you've got missing work.

05:08.891 --> 05:10.268
Hey, Chuck, what does that tell us?

05:12.103 --> 05:13.980
That you're not managing your time

05:14.397 --> 05:16.399
or maybe basketball
is taking too much of it.

05:16.399 --> 05:20.069
- Hey, babe, don't blame it on the game.
- I'm not blaming the game or the coach.

05:20.320 --> 05:23.656
But I'm reminding you that getting into
a good high school requires good grades.

05:24.115 --> 05:27.243
- JB, that proposal cannot be late.
- What proposal?

05:27.368 --> 05:30.580
Oh, it's our semester paper
for English class. The Passion Project.

05:30.913 --> 05:34.584
It's about what we'll do
when we get older, or what we love now.

05:35.293 --> 05:36.377
I'm doing hoops.

05:36.836 --> 05:39.297
Good man. Same for you, huh, JB?

05:41.174 --> 05:42.300
What else?

05:42.717 --> 05:45.261
Boy, if you miss this deadline,
you're gonna drop to a C.

05:45.261 --> 05:48.931
So turn it in before the Lakeside game
or you won't play.

05:49.557 --> 05:50.808
- What?
- What?

05:52.226 --> 05:54.854
- Chuck.
- You heard your mom. Come on now.

05:54.854 --> 05:56.397
I got a winning game plan,

05:56.564 --> 05:59.150
but my best shooter
is about to be benched?

05:59.275 --> 06:01.778
With Ace Howard,
head coach of Beacon Academy,

06:01.778 --> 06:02.904
sitting in the bleachers?

06:07.700 --> 06:08.910
Ace Howard's gonna be there?

06:09.035 --> 06:13.122
He has coached, like, five pro players!
We're talking NBA pipeline.

06:13.289 --> 06:14.957
He sees us beat the champs, and we're in!

06:15.208 --> 06:18.461
Yeah. Well, it starts with JB
beating this proposal.

06:18.461 --> 06:21.255
I am about GPA, not NBA.

06:21.255 --> 06:24.550
Mom, don't even worry about it, okay?
He's got this. I'll make sure of it.

06:25.093 --> 06:26.135
All right.

06:27.261 --> 06:29.597
Hey! Don't you dare eat both those,
put it down. Put it...

06:29.597 --> 06:30.765
Hey.
- Put it...

06:32.100 --> 06:34.685
- Put it down. Exactly...
- I'm eating you, right? Come on, girl.

06:35.061 --> 06:36.813
Okay.

06:49.283 --> 06:50.993
- Yo!
- Who are you texting?

06:50.993 --> 06:53.371
I'm not texting and why
are you snatching off my headphones?

06:53.371 --> 06:55.581
- Hey, you wanna hear my new beat?
- I wanna see you do your work.

06:55.915 --> 06:57.291
Look, that whole page is blank.

06:57.291 --> 07:00.878
- The passion proposal part is easy.
- You know I'm not good at papers.

07:02.839 --> 07:03.840
Check this out.

07:04.507 --> 07:06.426
Come on. Let me show you something.

07:07.468 --> 07:09.679
You're missing out on that beat.
I know "Headphones,"

07:09.679 --> 07:11.889
but this is what I do care about.

07:14.100 --> 07:16.853
Step one. Get into Beacon for high school.

07:17.228 --> 07:22.066
Step two. College ball. Final Four,
me versus you. I win.

07:22.191 --> 07:24.861
Step three. Get drafted to the Lakers.

07:25.153 --> 07:27.989
And step four.
Retiring to the NBA Hall of Fame

07:27.989 --> 07:29.198
as the new GOATs.

07:29.949 --> 07:31.242
You remember when we made this, right?

07:31.576 --> 07:33.411
I made it, you talked about it.

07:33.744 --> 07:35.496
And I never agreed
with all of step two, man.

07:36.080 --> 07:37.748
My bad, I just thought
it might inspire something.

07:38.166 --> 07:40.334
Bro, Dad is a baller
with a championship ring.

07:40.543 --> 07:41.961
That's inspiration enough.

07:44.046 --> 07:46.799
Look, you cannot miss this game, JB.

07:47.467 --> 07:49.552
Promise me that
that proposal's gonna be fire.

07:49.802 --> 07:51.512
It's gonna be lava, bro. Promise.

07:52.513 --> 07:53.764
Throwing socks now?

08:05.318 --> 08:06.819
What's up?
What's good, Vondie?

08:07.820 --> 08:08.821
Hey, Maya. Psych!

08:09.780 --> 08:11.115
- What's up, G?
- Okay.

08:13.910 --> 08:16.454
<i>Quick shoulder shake, a slick eye fake</i>

08:16.454 --> 08:18.623
<i>Oh, JB's too late</i>

08:18.789 --> 08:22.084
<i>Vondie's reading me like a book
But I got him shook</i>

08:22.335 --> 08:25.046
<i>'Cause his feet are the bank
And I am the...</i>

08:25.046 --> 08:26.088
Crook!

08:26.589 --> 08:29.008
You gotta work on those handles,
Langston Hughes.

08:29.008 --> 08:30.468
All that game

08:30.468 --> 08:32.345
- but Maya made you look lame.
- Whatever.

08:32.595 --> 08:35.473
<i>Maya the Defiant plus
Vondie the Giant</i>

08:35.765 --> 08:38.142
<i>make up this crew
like a superhero alliance.</i>

08:38.142 --> 08:41.020
All right, all right, all right,
Filthy, I'm on deadline for the paper.

08:41.354 --> 08:44.357
Lakeside beat you by 26
in last year's championship. Thoughts?

08:44.357 --> 08:46.734
- You can ask me. I was there, too.
- Yeah, but...

08:46.859 --> 08:49.487
Uh, your rival school led by Zuma Rivers,

08:49.487 --> 08:51.989
one of the top-most ranked players
in the state.

08:52.114 --> 08:53.699
Who nasty-dunked in your face.

08:53.824 --> 08:55.868
- Okay, really, bruh?
- Will Zuma best you again?

08:56.577 --> 08:58.955
<i>That fool's getting schooled, uncooled</i>

08:59.330 --> 09:02.583
<i>'Cause when Filthy gets hot
He got a slammerific shot</i>

09:02.792 --> 09:06.254
<i>It's supersonic sassy
Dunkalicious classy</i>

09:06.254 --> 09:09.757
<i>- And downright in your face McNasty!</i>
All right.

09:11.008 --> 09:11.884
<i>Good morning.</i>

09:12.510 --> 09:15.137
Ooh, someone is dressed for success.

09:15.137 --> 09:17.390
Interview with the superintendent
this afternoon.

09:17.807 --> 09:21.686
- Ooh. I am nervous.
- No, don't be.

09:21.686 --> 09:24.397
You're already doing the principal's job
in an acting capacity.

09:24.397 --> 09:25.565
- Oh!
- You've taught,

09:25.690 --> 09:27.942
you've been an administrator,
and the kids love you here.

09:27.942 --> 09:30.236
- Mm-hmm. Hey, hey, hey! Unless Cardi B

09:30.236 --> 09:31.445
is making a surprise appearance

09:31.445 --> 09:34.490
at the end of the hallway,
there is no running in it.

09:34.490 --> 09:36.951
Sorry Dr. Bell!
- But look, if she is, let me know. Okurr?

09:37.076 --> 09:40.580
Principal Bell
will not be denied.

09:40.705 --> 09:42.290
Hmm. Thank you, girl.

09:48.129 --> 09:49.880
What's up, little man?
Hey, Vondie.

09:54.093 --> 09:56.596
Hey! They got DJ Semple Plan
for the Fall Dance.

09:56.596 --> 09:58.389
Are you asking anyone to go, Filthy?

09:59.098 --> 10:00.850
Uh, no, I thought we were
all going together.

10:06.063 --> 10:07.648
- Josh?

10:07.940 --> 10:12.153
<i>Close your eyes, make a wish</i>

10:13.029 --> 10:16.907
<i>And blow out the candlelight</i>

10:17.033 --> 10:20.453
- Josh? Josh, say hello.

10:21.370 --> 10:23.497
Hi, Josh. Do you remember me?

10:23.873 --> 10:26.751
- What's up, Alexis? Do you go here now?
- Yeah. I just moved back.

10:26.876 --> 10:29.420
My parents split.
So now, I gotta split my time.

10:29.420 --> 10:32.548
- Oh, wow. I'm sorry to hear, Alexis.
It's okay, it happens.

10:33.049 --> 10:36.677
- Love the hair, Josh.
- Filthy's wings. They let him fly.

10:36.677 --> 10:40.056
Yeah, yeah, will you walk Alexis
to Ms. Rojas-Pierre's class please?

10:42.475 --> 10:43.643
Okay.

10:46.646 --> 10:47.730
Use your fingertips.

10:49.774 --> 10:50.858
<i>Pulchritudinous.</i>

10:51.651 --> 10:57.239
<i>Having great physical beauty or appeal.
As in, "Alexis was pulchritudinous."</i>

10:57.615 --> 11:01.494
<i>As in, "I'd never had a girlfriend
but if I did, she'd be pulchritudinous."</i>

11:07.375 --> 11:11.045
- Hey, he needs to align his chakras.
- No. He needs to bend his knees.

11:11.504 --> 11:12.838
Are you allergic to freebies?

11:13.172 --> 11:15.800
Come on, son. I want you
to shoot with the fingertips.

11:16.175 --> 11:17.968
All right, you square up, bend your knees.

11:17.968 --> 11:19.553
Bro, chill.
- Follow through. Hey!

11:20.805 --> 11:24.642
What are you doing? I'm over here
coming up with the Xs and Os for Lakeside.

11:24.767 --> 11:26.310
- And you're dancing?
- Come on Pops, I'm just...

11:26.435 --> 11:28.813
Okay, all of you,
I want you to run six laps

11:28.813 --> 11:31.691
while you wait your turn. Go!
Gio, get 'em, go!

11:31.691 --> 11:33.359
Come on! You heard the man.

11:33.484 --> 11:34.985
Let's go! Move, move.

11:37.363 --> 11:39.365
Look... (CLEARS THROAT) ...now I know

11:39.865 --> 11:43.661
that you're excited about Coach Howard
coming and getting into Beacon...

11:45.162 --> 11:48.457
but the big picture's for later.
Basketball rule number ten.

11:48.791 --> 11:52.086
It's one shot, one stop,
one game at a time.

11:54.463 --> 11:57.425
All right, run, run. Move, move! Groove!

12:02.430 --> 12:05.182
Chuck! Chuck!

12:05.349 --> 12:07.268
- Hey Chuck! Hey, you all right?
Dad! Dad, you good?

12:07.393 --> 12:09.687
- Yo, somebody call 911!

12:10.229 --> 12:12.273
All right, you're good. Hold on, Dad.

12:15.109 --> 12:16.819
<i>Despite everything going on,</i>

12:16.944 --> 12:19.238
<i>I know what Da Man would say.
"Keep ballin.</i>

12:19.947 --> 12:22.491
<i>"'Cause the minute you stop
playing your game, you already lost."</i>

12:22.616 --> 12:23.993
<i>Look, I don't care where we play.</i>

12:23.993 --> 12:25.745
<i>Yeah.
- All right, I'll beat the Bells</i>

12:25.745 --> 12:28.914
<i>at their house, our house,
or the Waffle House. All right?</i>

12:28.914 --> 12:34.128
<i>It's not a thing they can do.
Especially you, Filthy. Yeah, Lakeside!</i>

12:42.887 --> 12:44.930
- Dad.
Oh, boy!

12:45.389 --> 12:46.348
Hmm.

12:47.183 --> 12:49.018
What happened, Dad? You okay?
Yeah.

12:49.351 --> 12:51.312
I'm fine. I'm fine, okay?

12:52.438 --> 12:56.192
I'm fine. I'm Chuck "Da Man" Bell.
What do you kids say? I'm "Gucci"?

12:56.317 --> 12:59.612
Yes, kids said that, in elementary school.

12:59.612 --> 13:01.405
Oh, be nice.

13:03.115 --> 13:04.366
For real, Dad. Are you okay?

13:05.951 --> 13:08.204
- It was just an asthma attack.
Asthma?

13:08.537 --> 13:10.539
Asthma never sent you
to the hospital before.

13:10.539 --> 13:14.210
Look, your dad just needs rest
and a few days off. Okay?

13:15.711 --> 13:17.838
Few days? What about practice?

13:18.798 --> 13:19.924
For now, I'm on the bench.

13:20.257 --> 13:23.719
The bench? Dad, you're not coaching?
You've never not coached us.

13:23.719 --> 13:24.804
Gio can't coach!

13:24.970 --> 13:26.764
He doesn't even know the plays.
Not like you do.

13:26.764 --> 13:28.724
Okay, listen, he has my playbook.

13:28.974 --> 13:31.268
Unless his chakras is messed up,
you are good.

13:34.355 --> 13:37.107
Now, come on. The game is on soon.
We'll stop by Pollards' Wings,

13:37.483 --> 13:39.443
get the Wing-a-Palooza. Right?

13:39.819 --> 13:40.986
What kind you like?

13:42.655 --> 13:43.781
Fine.

13:43.906 --> 13:47.910
No Wing-a-Palooza.
I can't even watch the game?

13:48.035 --> 13:51.872
Not without acting
like a madman. You heard the doctor.

13:51.997 --> 13:56.085
- I've had asthma all my life, babe.
- It's not just that, and you know it.

13:56.627 --> 13:59.421
Your blood pressure's high.
Your cholesterol is ugly.

13:59.964 --> 14:01.423
Don't mess with me on this, Chuck.

14:01.924 --> 14:05.219
Your dad ignored all his symptoms
until it was too late to do anything.

14:05.761 --> 14:07.596
I know. All right.

14:08.430 --> 14:10.474
Oh, man. Wait, you missed your interview.

14:11.725 --> 14:13.227
Hand me the rest of the pillows.

14:14.144 --> 14:17.189
I, um, I... I went.

14:18.482 --> 14:19.483
And?

14:21.110 --> 14:22.319
And?

14:22.444 --> 14:24.697
And...

14:26.156 --> 14:27.283
I got the job.

14:27.449 --> 14:29.410
- You got the job?
- I got the job.

14:30.077 --> 14:31.287
- Babe, come here.
- Yeah.

14:31.287 --> 14:33.664
- I got the job.
- You Dr. Principal Bell?

14:33.789 --> 14:36.292
- You did it? Babe, I'm so proud of you.
-  Calm down.

14:36.292 --> 14:39.461
